main event: A large meteor or rocket was sighted traveling from South to North near Punta Campos, Mexico, with a duration of approximately 30-45 seconds.
interesting points: The report mentions that the sighting duration was too short for a rocket observation, suggesting the object was more likely a meteor.
The sighting was first reported by a Coast Guard station and later reported to intelligence staff of the USAF.
Unusually high mission GUP (Ground Unusual Phenomenon) near Punta Campos at an altitude of 3000 meters was noted on the same night as the sighting.
The object was described as moving rapidly, becoming a large motor or explosion, and then fading out of vision.
The report includes the OCR output indicating the reception and communication of the UFO sighting report.
